description:
&lt;p&gt;The Adult Intensive Care Unit offers an opportunity to gain knowledge and experience in cardiothoracic intensive care nursing at one of the country’s leading cardiorespiratory units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AICU is looking to recruit highly motivated, caring and compassionate band 5 staff nurses to work in our forward-thinking critical care unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit focus is on patient centred, research and evidence-based critical care, with a high element of multidisciplinary working in a friendly, modern environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;20 Bedded level 3 Cardiorespiratory ICU&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading centre in the critical care of patients requiring advanced cardiovascular support pre and post cardiac surgery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regional ECMO centre&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Specialist critical care services for patients with adult congenital heart disease, advanced lung disorders such as ILD and Cystic fibrosis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About you:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NMC Registered nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 Months minimum post qualifying experience in a relevant acute area (ICU/HDU/CCU, Acute ward)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A motivated, Enthusiastic, Hardworking and Caring individual who is keen to learn and develop.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The unit has a significant emphasis on education and training, with an experienced education team dedicated to nursing education and development. Successful applicants can expect a comprehensive package of induction and training to equip them with the knowledge and skills to care for complex cardiorespiratory critical care patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are encouraged&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For more information or to arrange an informal visit please contact Anoma Gunawardena: A.Gunawardena@rbht.nhs.uk or call 020 7352 8121 ext. 2331&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
